* Example 1: {@value} — refers to the value of this constant.
* Example 2: {@value #CONSTANT} — refers to another constant in the same class.
* Example 3: {@value com.example.Constants#TIMEOUT_MS} — fully qualified constant reference.
* Example 4: {@value %.2f} — formats this constant with two decimal places.
* Example 5: {@value %.2f com.example.Constants#PI} — formatted reference to an external constant.
* Example 6: {@value Constants#ENCODING} — class reference using unqualified class name (must be imported or in same package).
* Example 7: {@value %.1f Constants#MEMORY_MB} — formatted with thousands separator and one decimal place.
* Example 8: {@value %.2f
*               com.example.Constants#PI} — formatted reference to an external constant.
* Example 9: {@value
*               %.2f
*               com.example.Constants#PI} — formatted reference to an external constant.
